Having patronized Papaye Restaurant for some months now, I must say that I was very displeased with their service yesterday. It was one of those evenings, and I decided to place an order to be delivered. I ordered a plate of small jollof with goat meat, plantains, and puff puff on the side. The order went through and I waited patiently for delivery; upon delivery and getting to take out my order from its packaging, I noticed that my order was brought incomplete. I placed a quick call to the guy who delivered my order, and while he didn't respond, I decided to call the restaurant directly to report this observation. I informed them that the following were missing: 2 orders of puff puff, which will be 4 in total, and plantains, which I paid for 9 pieces but only received 3. I was told that they were out of puff puff and made the decision to send me "Kebab" instead. I asked why I wasn't called in the first place to inform before making decisions for something I was paying for. The representative from the restaurant then proceeded to tell me that I was going to get a call back to resolve the situation. Guys, would you believe that up until now, I am yet to receive a call, and to make matters worse, not even a single apology was rendered. At this point, I have decided not to patronize this restaurant again since the service is nothing to write home about. Papaye, very wrong and unprofessional move.
